<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="533" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,438,1089]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,438,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The gonostylus, which is strongly bent and evenly broadened from the base to the middle, has a bipartite pectinate claw apically (
<figureCitation box="[537,630,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,209,1438]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male morphology of Bernadottea natalenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175080/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Of the gonocoxites, the ventral emargination is shallow, broadly Vshaped and strongly sclerotized at the base (
<figureCitation box="[657,747,513,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,209,1438]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male morphology of Bernadottea natalenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175080/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
, ↓2), and the medial bridges are provided with long, curved, glabrous processes (↓3). The tegmen, whose apex is a rounded cap of complicated structure (
<figureCitation box="[1257,1351,552,577]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,209,1438]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male morphology of Bernadottea natalenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175080/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
, ↓4), is provided with a pair of strongly sclerotized, ventrally directed processes mediolaterally (↓5). The aedeagal bulge is conspicuous by the presence of numerous, small spikes covering its ventral surface (
<figureCitation box="[1096,1183,629,654]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,209,1438]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male morphology of Bernadottea natalenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175080/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
, ↓6).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,438,1089]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,414,665,690]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Other characters.</emphasis>
Body size 
<quantity box="[552,645,666,690]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="533" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[660,731,665,690]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Head.</emphasis>
Eye bridge 2–3 ommatidia long dorsally. Flagellomeres 11; apical flagellomere simple; neck of fourth flagellomere 0.9 times as long as node (
<figureCitation box="[1070,1158,701,726]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,209,1438]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male morphology of Bernadottea natalenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175080/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1176,1241,701,726]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1256,1321,701,726]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[168,1367,353,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[157,1398,339,1930]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male habitus of Bernadottea natalenSiS. Holotype mounted in Canada balsam, partly rearranged and completed, one set of bodyappendages and parts of vestiture omitted.Scale 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175078/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). R1 = 3.5 times Rs. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[265,388,740,765]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Abdomen.</emphasis>
First tergite asetose; second to eighth tergites with a few lateral and no dorsal setae; pleural membrane asetose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[377,494,776,801]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Lateral lobes of ninth tergite small, rounded, microtrichose, space between lobes larger than their width (
<figureCitation box="[414,502,812,837]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,209,1438]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male morphology of Bernadottea natalenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175080/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites: ventral portions extensively, darkly pigmented around emargination and along longitudinal axis, pointed posteriorly; dorsal portions with subrectangular lobes posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1332,1423,848,873]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,209,1438]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male morphology of Bernadottea natalenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175080/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Gonostylar apex subrectangular, compressed laterally resulting in wedge-shape; outer claw twice the size of inner claw (
<figureCitation box="[219,309,920,945]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1470,1492]" captionTargetBox="[175,1419,209,1438]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1449]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male morphology of Bernadottea natalenSiS (holotype). A: Gonostylus, dorsal. B: Ninth tergite, dorsal. C: Genitalia, ventral.D: Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme, ventral.E: Fourth flagellomere, lateral.Scales 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1175080/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct broadly rounded posteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="533" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,438,1089]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,956,981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is derived from Natal, a now historical name of South Africa’s eastern province 
<collectingRegion box="[256,435,992,1017]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">KwaZulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
, where the 
<typeStatus box="[562,660,992,1017]" pageId="4" pageNumber="533">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
